One published novel (
                     George Wendern Gave a Party
                  ) is attributed to the pseudonym John Inglis; three other works are attributed to the presumed pseudonyms Leonard Carter, John Marison and Gerard Mountjoy. One script (
                     An Interlude
                  ) is co-authored with Walter Herries Pollock and one cinema scenario (
                     Woodside Farm
                  ) is co-authored with Millicent Wadham.

Based on a novel (1902) of the same name (published in the U.S. as 
                           Margaret Vincent
                        )
